### 10. Key Differences: Hook-Level vs API-Level Mocking

| Aspect | Hook-Level (vi.mock) | API-Level (vi.mock) |
|--------|------------------|-----------------|
| **What's mocked** | React hooks (useMarkets, useSession, etc.) | API client functions (listMarkets, getMarket, etc.) |
| **Mock location** | `/lib/query/hooks`, `/features/*/context` | `/lib/api/client` |
| **When to use** | Component tests that depend on data fetching | Page/route tests, simpler component tests |
| **Setup complexity** | Higher - need default return values for each hook | Lower - can mock entire module at once |
| **Test files** | BayesNetGraph, ConditionalEditor, VariableRow, etc. | Portfolio, MarketDetail, MarketList, System |
| **Return types** | Full hook object (isLoading, data, error, etc.) | Direct response objects |

